15#ifndef DNS_RDATASETITER_H
16#define DNS_RDATASETITER_H 1
17
18/*****
19 ***** Module Info
20 *****/
21
22/*! \file dns/rdatasetiter.h
23 * \brief
24 * The DNS Rdataset Iterator interface allows iteration of all of the
25 * rdatasets at a node.
26 *
27 * The dns_rdatasetiter_t type is like a "virtual class". To actually use
28 * it, an implementation of the class is required. This implementation is
29 * supplied by the database.
30 *
31 * It is the client's responsibility to call dns_rdataset_disassociate()
32 * on all rdatasets returned.
33 *
34 * XXX more XXX
35 *
36 * MP:
37 *\li The iterator itself is not locked. The caller must ensure
38 * synchronization.
39 *
40 *\li The iterator methods ensure appropriate database locking.
41 *
42 * Reliability:
43 *\li No anticipated impact.
44 *
45 * Resources:
46 *\li TBS
47 *
48 * Security:
49 *\li No anticipated impact.
50 *
51 * Standards:
52 *\li None.
53 */
54
55/*****
56 ***** Imports
57 *****/
58
59#include <isc/lang.h>
60#include <isc/magic.h>
61#include <isc/stdtime.h>
62
63#include <dns/types.h>
64
65ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
66
67/*****
68 ***** Types
69 *****/
70
71typedef struct dns_rdatasetitermethods {
72 void (*destroy)(dns_rdatasetiter_t **iteratorp);
73 isc_result_t (*first)(dns_rdatasetiter_t *iterator);
74 isc_result_t (*next)(dns_rdatasetiter_t *iterator);
75 void (*current)(dns_rdatasetiter_t *iterator,
76 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
77} dns_rdatasetitermethods_t;
78
79#define DNS_RDATASETITER_MAGIC ISC_MAGIC('D','N','S','i')
80#define DNS_RDATASETITER_VALID(i) ISC_MAGIC_VALID(i, DNS_RDATASETITER_MAGIC)
81
82/*%
83 * This structure is actually just the common prefix of a DNS db
84 * implementation's version of a dns_rdatasetiter_t.
85 * \brief
86 * Direct use of this structure by clients is forbidden. DB implementations
87 * may change the structure. 'magic' must be #DNS_RDATASETITER_MAGIC for
88 * any of the dns_rdatasetiter routines to work. DB implementations must
89 * maintain all DB rdataset iterator invariants.
90 */
91struct dns_rdatasetiter {
92 /* Unlocked. */
93 unsigned int magic;
94 dns_rdatasetitermethods_t * methods;
95 dns_db_t * db;
96 dns_dbnode_t * node;
97 dns_dbversion_t * version;
98 isc_stdtime_t now;
99};
100
101void
102dns_rdatasetiter_destroy(dns_rdatasetiter_t **iteratorp);
103/*%<
104 * Destroy '*iteratorp'.
105 *
106 * Requires:
107 *
108 *\li '*iteratorp' is a valid iterator.
109 *
110 * Ensures:
111 *
112 *\li All resources used by the iterator are freed.
113 *
114 *\li *iteratorp == NULL.
115 */
116
117isc_result_t
118dns_rdatasetiter_first(dns_rdatasetiter_t *iterator);
119/*%<
120 * Move the rdataset cursor to the first rdataset at the node (if any).
121 *
122 * Requires:
123 *\li 'iterator' is a valid iterator.
124 *
125 * Returns:
126 *\li ISC_R_SUCCESS
127 *\li ISC_R_NOMORE There are no rdatasets at the node.
128 *
129 *\li Other results are possible, depending on the DB implementation.
130 */
131
132isc_result_t
133dns_rdatasetiter_next(dns_rdatasetiter_t *iterator);
134/*%<
135 * Move the rdataset cursor to the next rdataset at the node (if any).
136 *
137 * Requires:
138 *\li 'iterator' is a valid iterator.
139 *
140 * Returns:
141 *\li ISC_R_SUCCESS
142 *\li ISC_R_NOMORE There are no more rdatasets at the
143 * node.
144 *
145 *\li Other results are possible, depending on the DB implementation.
146 */
147
148void
149dns_rdatasetiter_current(dns_rdatasetiter_t *iterator,
150 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
151/*%<
152 * Return the current rdataset.
153 *
154 * Requires:
155 *\li 'iterator' is a valid iterator.
156 *
157 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid, disassociated rdataset.
158 *
159 *\li The rdataset cursor of 'iterator' is at a valid location (i.e. the
160 * result of last call to a cursor movement command was #ISC_R_SUCCESS).
161 */
162
163ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS
164
165#endif /* DNS_RDATASETITER_H */
